properties.Name: MedicalReport
properties.Description:
A report submitted to an insurer that supplies medical data on life and health insurance applicants.

Most companies establish for larger policies a medical report requirement to provide additional underwriting information.

Medical reports must be completed by a qualified individual, but that person does not have to be a physician. For example, companies typically accept reports that are completed by a paramedic or nurse.

Columns.Name: MedicalReportId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Medical Report.

Columns.Name: MedicalReportDate
Columns.Description: The date of the Medical Report.

Columns.Name: MedicalReportStatement
Columns.Description: A statement, comments or additional information regarding the associated Medical Report.

Columns.Name: MedicalReportReviewedByInsurerDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Medical Report was reviewed by the Insurer.

Columns.Name: MedicalReportReviewedByInsurerName
Columns.Description: The name of the Insurer representative reviewing the Medical Report.

Columns.Name: MedicalReportReviewedByInsurerTitle
Columns.Description: The title of the Insurer person or representative reviewing the Medical Report.

Columns.Name: AttendingPhysiciansStatement
Columns.Description: The Attending Physician's Statement provides details about the medical condition(s) in question.

Columns.Name: InsurancePolicyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Policy.
